```xml
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.igscheduledpostingto">

    <!-- 
        The AndroidManifest.xml file defines essential information about your app.
        This configuration ensures optimal performance and efficiency for the 
        "ig scheduled posting tool - Android Automation Tool."
    -->

    <!-- Declare necessary permissions to enhance application functionality -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <!-- 
        Achieves seamless connectivity with social media platforms.
        Improves efficiency by allowing content scheduling and management 
        operations without interruptions.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- 
        Enables access to storage for managing scheduled posts and media.
        Increases performance by allowing the app to retrieve user content
        directly from storage, thus enhancing user experience.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- 
        Allows the application to save media files efficiently.
        Boosts results by enabling the tool to store and manage content effectively.
    -->

    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="ig scheduled posting tool - Android Automation Tool"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.DayNight.NoActionBar">

        <!-- 
            Registering the main activity that serves as the entry point for the application.
            Enhances capabilities by providing a user-friendly interface for content management.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            Registering the automation service that handles background operations for scheduled 
            posts. Supports 24/7 automated operations, maximizing efficiency and effectiveness
            of social media management.
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService" 
                 android:exported="false">
            <!-- 
                This service runs in the background, enhancing performance by managing content 
                posting without user intervention, ensuring timely social media engagement.
            -->
        </service>

    </application>
</manifest>
```

### Summary of Key Benefits:
- **Internet Permission**: Enables seamless connectivity for automated operations, ensuring uninterrupted functionality.
- **Storage Permissions**: Facilitate efficient management of user content, improving the overall user experience.
- **MainActivity & AutomationService**: These components provide a robust infrastructure for efficient social media management and automation, enhancing user engagement through timely content scheduling and posting.

This configuration effectively supports the MadHub automation tool's objectives, ensuring compliance with platform requirements while delivering exceptional performance and efficiency in managing social media activities.
